The paper discusses the efficient management of pilot contamination in massive MIMO systems, which is a topic related to information theory (cs.IT), network infrastructure (cs.NI), and system engineering (cs.SY). The paper also evaluates the performance of various allocation strategies, which involves mathematical modeling and analysis, making it relevant to multimedia (cs.MM) and architecture (cs.AR) sub-categories.
